Integument
. Color dark brown. Body surface and pteromorphs punctate (visible under high magnification, × 
1000
). Rostrum and anterior ventral tectum with sparse round foveoles (up to 
4
). Notogaster and anogenital region with well developed cerotegument, represent by thick, blocky structure, with including round foveoles (up to 
12
). Prodorsum, and epimeral and lateral podosomal regions with thin, gel-like cerotegument.

